OL,3,CCraig Bellamy 'grateful' to be
OL,4,Cappointed as new Wales manager
OL,6,FHe continued: "Wales has always been
OL,7,Freally important to me. I've spent a
OL,8,Flot of my career away from here as
OL,9,Fwell and obviously I've had certain
OL,10,Fperiods where I've been here but I was
OL,11,Fborn here, I've spent a lot of my
OL,12,Fcareer away from here and the
OL,13,Fopportunity led to lead your national
OL,14,Fteam is rare and to get it as a first
OL,15,Fopportunity.
OL,17,F"It became clear to me that if there
OL,18,Fwas an opportunity to do this, this is
OL,19,Fthe one I wanted and I'm grateful for
OL,20,Fthat."
